TextBlock.TextLine: In Antwarp 8 d 1681
London Henry Maynard
Sr. my last to you was on the first curitt sence recd. yd of 24: past I have payd
the £85:- you drew on the heires of mad bouwelis, so have made you
debter onmy acctt. for the netto £85:- which please to transfers accordingly
and when receaveyd rest of them, shall note that on yd acctt. lekhoven
heengout of towne, will continue about 3 weeles before I shall
receav the rest, & haveing payd the whole bill can not part hem
£54:15:3 as you order butt onely receave the ballance due to you,
for they would not paythe the £85:- a governo - seeng, you found o
what kersies to my direction, you did well to buynow as for the
frensh, as yett wee have about 2 months to conssidder whilst all
the spanish forces are drawing togheter to hinder their inter prises, I van
not yett perceav any feare for badd debts in walled townes, & in the countrey
I ge butt little or no creditt & though wee should be frenchified yett no feare
neather rthe worst of all is, that the continuall allarmes, keeps back the
sale as much as mony & wee might suffer some thing by beeng out of
mony butt Ihope not in the leastaly bad deots, haveing (god be thanhed I last
notthing yett: inclosed are the acctt. of sale of sber & which please
to peruse & finding wright advise mee when you come over r you shall
finde as well the genall as & acctt. curitt cally, beeng butt littlever
nothing behinde in mj bookes, & when you have provided the 10 desired
pack whites you may make up my ccatt or rather bring itt with you
att yd coming over & intend to inorder no more goods sunlles you pleyd
to be speake 5 russ whites 6 N silver markes more of the broad lists for
the besuites will not alter their custome of haveing goods as they are
used to I do much wonder that amonghst the 5 broad lists there
should be difference in goodnes seenghis one the sume hand the made
them I wish they prove well, & hope you had not the refusall proy
endeavour to persuade the maker to deliver p all of of one goodnets
& take no narrow lists more till I see these 2 already ship: E have given
you creditt for the goods aboard klarck god send him wel over: you did
much better to make 2 little packes then to rem the resico of beeng
opened aboad of the ships dispatch the E &WW. pack what is as sorne
as you finde convenient. Richd pindar is well arrived, as also how lotson
butt not yett the goods neither anynews of the rest mr f. bandier
wrott mee that r. furnase ordered him for £40 more so the
the whole will come to no less then £300 which must be payd
reaady so that I shall not be in acondition to remitt you as yett, butth
withhin shall remitt you att sight for my acctt. which will serve you
before yd going away there foredo mee the favour not to draw on mee
not doubting butt that I shall remitt more then £30 £400: which
I hope will give you content for I can not adide drawing: you ay
be assured if any alteration of warrs should happenthat I shall
take good care ford intrest &wrott thes day all that is needfull
to r. shaughter andercouert of in. peeters pray endeavour anend
according to my preposition for they are reall spoore & shall att last
have hible or nothing to ave I hope you will be good medeaborfr
I have don all I could, & am much desired there unto & do
petty them for really I have no other intrest in the buslynes
butt to help my freinds & to cleared of that concerne

Richd pindar is well arrived, butt the goods are not come yett I hope you have
given order for 60: white bayes more according to formar directions
of which you made no mention a long while if you h in formed
that bayes are pleat & reasonable cheapprovide 1oo p. assort
fyoum 34 s toso ap to have with the first vessel some
att least && then wee will in order no more till towards next spring i
whilst in the meane while Illdo all endeavour I can to makes the best
of our goods & to prepare what mony I can to give you content & sot
pray advise mee if you intend to como over or no, that in case not

Sr. my last to you was on the first acctt. with invoyce for 2 packett of laces of
which I hope N.4 safe att doner before now N.5 must be att neuwporte by thes
time, I have yeasterday past my bill ou you att 2 uso for £89:10:11 in favour
of the widdow of Egidins van laer att 35:4 which is £158:44 flemish
the invoyce beeng £158:2 to which added 2 brokidge makes saie suce

which please to give due honour, now receaved yd of 21: past accordingly
to which shall provide the needfull, beengvere well auquanted with
the sorts you meane, of which shall endeavourto provide such that
no other shall out do you, butt must have some xas0 dayis te provide
itt other wise if ell take asitt comes I can not so well p lease

mons. inantwoort aenden ul van gisteren segge dat derattiener noch niet en
sijn gekomen, maereven wel hope de selve naeste weke hier sullen sijn alrwanne
sonder foute 3 aen ul sal senden, waer op moght verlaten in gesloten sijn2
staelen van de 2 leste witte grijse die ick bij mij sel hebbe, de selve hen ul
laten a 45 stuijvers p elle op rabat midts ul die beyde gelieft te hebbe, soo
gelieft mij cito te antwoorden, ofte de selve ul konnen dienen, ofte soo niet
sal andere middelsoeken omul te gerieven soo verwaght hier op ul

meiouff. alhoewel ick hier de kanten seer goede koop bevinde nochtans hebb
goet gedaght van ul noch een prenve te wagen met hope van beter succhh
als voor desen: oversulx kan ul mij dienen doet het soo now als mogelijk is
want ick dagelijke veel van doen hebbe, ende wetr het ul weldoen kan
soo wanneer opt nowst wilt overlete soo seijnt mij de onderscreven
stucken volgens het in geleyt stael, die ul heeft gereet oft salt
bekomen het en komt op 3 a 4 dagen niet aen, want ick wat goedt
wit en goeden koop geirne hadde soo stelt alles als hetwesen moet
